The paper discusses a novel cloud-based HyperOpt framework for machine learning, which suggests that it falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on hyperparameter optimization, which is a common problem in deep learning, and thus, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses applications of the framework in image recognition and question-answering, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the incorporation of the framework with any cloud platform, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or software engineering (cs.SE).
